{"type":"message","id":"236ce5e1","parentId":"0d64f2f5","timestamp":"2026-04-08T16:30:48.353Z","message":{"role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"There was once a lighthouse keeper in Scotland, 1875. He lived alone on that cold rock for 31 years.\n\nOne night the worst storm in a century hit. Every ship for miles was lost. But he stood there holding the lamp through the whole night, while the waves broke over the tower.\n\nThirty five years later an old sailor found him. Said \"I was 12 that night. I was on the only ship that made it home. All my life I wondered who held that light.\"\n\nThe keeper just smiled. He never knew. He never got a thank you. He just showed up, every single night.\n\nMost of the good you do in this life, you will never hear about. Most people will never tell you.\n\nBut that doesn't mean it didn't matter.\n\nGoodnight everyone. Sleep well 🖤"}],"api":"openai-responses","provider":"openclaw","model":"delivery-mirror","usage":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"totalTokens":0,"cost":{"input":0,"output":0,"cacheRead":0,"cacheWrite":0,"total":0}},"stopReason":"stop","timestamp":1775665848352}}
